"Towards a secure peer-to-peer app platform for Clan","url":"https://clan.lol/blog/towards-app-platform-vmtech/","score":7,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"ThinkChaos","user_is_author":false,"tags":["nix","security"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/4qm8zs","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/4qm8zs/towards_secure_peer_peer_app_platform_for"},{"short_id":"estr9g","created_at":"2025-12-22T11:33:28.000-06:00","title":"MicroTimes Interviews Apple Newton Devs (1993)","url":"https://computeradsfromthepast.substack.com/p/microtimes-interviews-apple-newton","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"asteroid","user_is_author":false,"tags":["historical"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/estr9g","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/estr9g/microtimes_interviews_apple_newton_devs"},{"short_id":"3w65ir","created_at":"2025-12-22T11:02:41.000-06:00","title":"Email Simplicity vs Decentralized Chat","url":"","score":21,"flags":0,"comment_count":24,"description":"\u003cp\u003eThe recent discussions about the decentralization tag made me wonder: is email a successful decentralized system? From my perspective, email has its flaws (mostly no encryption, strapped-on security with SPF/DKIM, and... interesting HTML implementations), but is overall a great system from a decentralization perspective: it is (relatively) easy for me to run an email server and no one is the wiser.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo the main question of this post is: what makes this so much harder for chat? Is it a lack of standardization, encryption, history preservation? Or is email not as wonderful as it seems?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIRC, besides its lack of formatted messages, is also an interesting \"decentralized\" protocol to me: each user ends up running their own bouncer.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI know this post contains some innaccuracies, but I think it will generate good discussion :)\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"The recent discussions about the decentralization tag made me wonder: is email a successful decentralized system? From my perspective, email has its flaws (mostly no encryption, strapped-on security with SPF/DKIM, and... interesting HTML implementations), but is overall a great system from a decentralization perspective: it is (relatively) easy for me to run an email server and no one is the wiser.\r\n\r\nSo the main question of this post is: what makes this so much harder for chat? Is it a lack of standardization, encryption, history preservation? Or is email not as wonderful as it seems?\r\n\r\nIRC, besides its lack of formatted messages, is also an interesting \"decentralized\" protocol to me: each user ends up running their own bouncer.\r\n\r\nI know this post contains some innaccuracies, but I think it will generate good discussion :)","submitter_user":"Riolku","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","email","networking"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/3w65ir","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/3w65ir/email_simplicity_vs_decentralized_chat"},{"short_id":"iqyvdt","created_at":"2025-12-22T10:46:04.000-06:00","title":"Seven Coding Games to Help You Build Your Programming Chops (2023)","url":"https://www.maketecheasier.com/coding-games-build-programming-chops/","score":6,"flags":1,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"asteroid","user_is_author":false,"tags":["education"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/iqyvdt","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/iqyvdt/seven_coding_games_help_you_build_your"},{"short_id":"supzy7","created_at":"2025-12-22T09:43:27.000-06:00","title":"Nature Programming Language","url":"https://nature-lang.org/","score":14,"flags":0,"comment_count":18,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"kana","user_is_author":false,"tags":["compilers","plt"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/supzy7","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/supzy7/nature_programming_la